      "source": [
        "# Deep Learning for Alzheimer's Binary Classification\n",
        "**Author:** Carlos Roberto Souza Garcia Filho\n",
        "**Context:** Master's in Data Engineering and Data Science (UTAD)\n",
        "\n",
        "## üìå Objective\n",
        "This project aims to classify MRI brain scans into two specific categories:\n",
        "1.  **ND (Non-Demented):** Healthy patients.\n",
        "2.  **VMD (Very Mild Demented):** Patients in the early stages of Alzheimer's Disease.\n",
        "\n",
        "The primary goal is to minimize **False Negatives**, ensuring that patients with early signs of dementia are correctly identified for further medical diagnosis.\n",
        "\n",
        "## ‚öôÔ∏è Initial Setup"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "z-FXr64mp7Yh"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import kagglehub\n",
        "import os\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "import seaborn as sns\n",
        "import random\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow import keras\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras import layers, models\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.preprocessing.image import ImageDataGenerator\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.callbacks import EarlyStopping\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.optimizers import Adam\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, confusion_matrix, recall_score, accuracy_score\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import BatchNormalization, Activation\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.applications.vgg16 import VGG16, preprocess_input\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fixing seeds for reproduction\n",
        "SEED = 42\n",
        "os.environ['PYTHONHASHSEED'] = str(SEED)\n",
        "random.seed(SEED)\n",
        "np.random.seed(SEED)\n",
        "tf.random.set_seed(SEED)\n",
        "print(f\"Random Seed set to: {SEED}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 1. Dataset Download ---\n",
        "print(\"Downloading dataset...\")\n",
        "dataset_path = kagglehub.dataset_download(\"kanaadlimaye/alzheimers-classification-dataset\")\n",
        "print(f\"Dataset ready at: {dataset_path}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 2. Global Constants ---\n",
        "IMAGE_SIZE = 224\n",
        "BATCH_SIZE = 32\n",
        "CHANNELS = 3\n",
        "EPOCHS = 50\n",
        "SELECTED_CLASSES = ['ND', 'VMD'] # Binary Classification\n",
        "\n",
        "# Paths\n",
        "SOURCE_BASE_DIR = os.path.join(dataset_path, 'Alzheimers_Detection_dataset')\n",
        "TRAIN_IMG_DIR = os.path.join(SOURCE_BASE_DIR, 'train')\n",
        "VAL_IMG_DIR = os.path.join(SOURCE_BASE_DIR, 'valid')\n",
        "TEST_IMG_DIR = os.path.join(SOURCE_BASE_DIR, 'test')\n",
        "CSV_DIR = os.path.join(SOURCE_BASE_DIR, 'CSV_datafiles')\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 3. Helper Function for Plots ---\n",
        "def plot_history(history, model_name):\n",
        "    acc = history.history['accuracy']\n",
        "    val_acc = history.history['val_accuracy']\n",
        "    loss = history.history['loss']\n",
        "    val_loss = history.history['val_loss']\n",
        "    epochs = range(1, len(acc) + 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 5))\n",
        "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs, acc, 'b-', label='Training')\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs, val_acc, 'r-', label='Validation')\n",
        "    plt.title(f'Accuracy - {model_name}')\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "\n",
        "    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs, loss, 'b-', label='Training')\n",
        "    plt.plot(epochs, val_loss, 'r-', label='Validation')\n",
        "    plt.title(f'Loss - {model_name}')\n",
        "    plt.legend()\n",
        "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- 4. Helper Function to Load Dataframes ---\n",
        "def load_and_filter(csv_path):\n",
        "    df = pd.read_csv(csv_path)\n",
        "    class_columns = ['MD', 'MoD', 'ND', 'VMD']\n",
        "    df['label'] = df[class_columns].idxmax(axis=1)\n",
        "    return df[df['label'].isin(SELECTED_CLASSES)].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "df_train = load_and_filter(os.path.join(CSV_DIR, '_train_classes.csv'))\n",
        "df_val = load_and_filter(os.path.join(CSV_DIR, '_valid_classes.csv'))\n",
        "df_test = load_and_filter(os.path.join(CSV_DIR, '_test_classes.csv'))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"Data Loaded: Train={len(df_train)}, Val={len(df_val)}, Test={len(df_test)}\")"
      ],

    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## üß™ Experiment 1: Baseline Model\n",
        "We establish a performance benchmark using a simple CNN (2 convolutional blocks) with basic image rescaling."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "-zRJID1CqP7Q"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Simple Generators (Rescale Only)\n",
        "datagen_base = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255.)\n",
        "\n",
        "train_gen = datagen_base.flow_from_dataframe(df_train, TRAIN_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
        "val_gen = datagen_base.flow_from_dataframe(df_val, VAL_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)\n",
        "test_gen = datagen_base.flow_from_dataframe(df_test, TEST_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Baseline Architecture\n",
        "model_base = models.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.Input(shape=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model_base.compile(optimizer=Adam(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Training\n",
        "print(\"Training Baseline Model...\")\n",
        "history_base = model_base.fit(train_gen, validation_data=val_gen, epochs=EPOCHS, callbacks=[EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)], verbose=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Evaluation\n",
        "plot_history(history_base, \"Baseline\")\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Baseline Report ---\")\n",
        "test_gen.reset() # Garante a ordem correta\n",
        "y_pred_base = (model_base.predict(test_gen) > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()\n",
        "print(classification_report(test_gen.classes, y_pred_base, target_names=list(test_gen.class_indices.keys())))"
      ],

      "source": [
        "### Baseline Analysis\n",
        "The model achieved high accuracy, but the loss curves indicate rapid **overfitting** starting around epoch 6.\n",
        "\n",
        "## üß™ Experiment 2: Data Augmentation\n",
        "To combat overfitting, we apply random transformations (rotation, zoom, flip) to the training images to artificially increase dataset diversity."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RWr89IhWqT-M"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Generator with Augmentation\n",
        "datagen_aug = ImageDataGenerator(\n",
        "    rescale=1./255., rotation_range=20, width_shift_range=0.1,\n",
        "    height_shift_range=0.1, shear_range=0.1, zoom_range=0.1,\n",
        "    horizontal_flip=True, fill_mode='nearest'\n",
        ")\n",
        "# Note: Validation and Test sets should never be augmented\n",
        "datagen_no_aug = ImageDataGenerator(rescale=1./255.)\n",
        "\n",
        "train_gen_aug = datagen_aug.flow_from_dataframe(df_train, TRAIN_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
        "val_gen = datagen_no_aug.flow_from_dataframe(df_val, VAL_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Architecture (Same as Baseline)\n",
        "model_aug = models.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.Input(shape=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "    layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(128, activation='relu'),\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model_aug.compile(optimizer=Adam(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Training\n",
        "print(\"Training with Data Augmentation...\")\n",
        "history_aug = model_aug.fit(train_gen_aug, validation_data=val_gen, epochs=EPOCHS, callbacks=[EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)], verbose=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Evaluation\n",
        "plot_history(history_aug, \"Data Augmentation\")\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Data Augmentation Report ---\")\n",
        "test_gen.reset()\n",
        "y_pred_aug = (model_aug.predict(test_gen) > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()\n",
        "print(classification_report(test_gen.classes, y_pred_aug, target_names=list(test_gen.class_indices.keys())))"
      ],

        "### Augmentation Analysis\n",
        "Result: The transformations were too aggressive for this simple model capacity, preventing effective learning.\n",
        "\n",
        "## üß™ Experiment 3: Deep CNN + BatchNom + Dropout\n",
        "Here, we increase model capacity to learn more complex features, but we introduce **Dropout (0.5)** as a robust regularization technique."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "EBVNtAPnqXWv"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Use simple generators (no aggressive augmentation)\n",
        "train_gen = datagen_base.flow_from_dataframe(df_train, TRAIN_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Deep Architecture with Dropout + BatchNormalization\n",
        "model_deep = models.Sequential([\n",
        "    layers.Input(shape=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS)),\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Block 1\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(32, (3, 3), padding='same'),\n",
        "    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n",
        "    layers.Activation('relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Block 2\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(64, (3, 3), padding='same'),\n",
        "    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n",
        "    layers.Activation('relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Block 3\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(128, (3, 3), padding='same'),\n",
        "    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n",
        "    layers.Activation('relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Block 4\n",
        "    layers.Conv2D(256, (3, 3), padding='same'),\n",
        "    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n",
        "    layers.Activation('relu'),\n",
        "    layers.MaxPooling2D((2, 2)),\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Flatten(),\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Dense(256),\n",
        "    layers.BatchNormalization(),\n",
        "    layers.Activation('relu'),\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Dropout(0.5),\n",
        "\n",
        "    layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')\n",
        "])\n",
        "\n",
        "model_deep.compile(optimizer=Adam(learning_rate=0.0001), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Training\n",
        "print(\"Training Improved Deep Model...\")\n",
        "history_deep = model_deep.fit(train_gen, validation_data=val_gen, epochs=EPOCHS, callbacks=[EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=6, restore_best_weights=True)], verbose=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Evaluation\n",
        "plot_history(history_deep, \"Deep + BatchNom + Dropout\")\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Deep + BatchNom + Dropout Report ---\")\n",
        "test_gen.reset()\n",
        "y_pred_deep = (model_deep.predict(test_gen) > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()\n",
        "print(classification_report(test_gen.classes, y_pred_deep, target_names=list(test_gen.class_indices.keys())))"
      ],

        "### Deep + Dropout Analysis\n",
        "**Best Result.** The model achieved ~98% accuracy with perfect generalization (train and validation curves aligned). Crucially, the number of False Negatives was low.\n",

        "## üß™ Experiment 4: Transfer Learning (VGG16)\n",
        "We test a pre-trained VGG16 model (frozen weights) to check if generic features are suitable for this task."
      ],

      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# 1. Generators with VGG16 Preprocessing\n",
        "datagen_vgg = ImageDataGenerator(preprocessing_function=preprocess_input)\n",
        "\n",
        "train_gen_vgg = datagen_vgg.flow_from_dataframe(df_train, TRAIN_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=True)\n",
        "val_gen_vgg = datagen_vgg.flow_from_dataframe(df_val, VAL_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)\n",
        "test_gen_vgg = datagen_vgg.flow_from_dataframe(df_test, TEST_IMG_DIR, x_col='filename', y_col='label', target_size=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE), classes=SELECTED_CLASSES, class_mode='binary', batch_size=BATCH_SIZE, shuffle=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Frozen VGG16 Model\n",
        "base_model = VGG16(input_shape=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS), include_top=False, weights='imagenet')\n",
        "base_model.trainable = False\n",
        "\n",
        "inputs = layers.Input(shape=(IMAGE_SIZE, IMAGE_SIZE, CHANNELS))\n",
        "x = base_model(inputs, training=False)\n",
        "x = layers.Flatten()(x)\n",
        "x = layers.Dense(256, activation='relu')(x)\n",
        "x = layers.Dropout(0.5)(x)\n",
        "outputs = layers.Dense(1, activation='sigmoid')(x)\n",
        "\n",
        "model_vgg = models.Model(inputs, outputs)\n",
        "model_vgg.compile(optimizer=Adam(), loss='binary_crossentropy', metrics=['accuracy'])\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. Training\n",
        "print(\"Training VGG16 Transfer Learning...\")\n",
        "history_vgg = model_vgg.fit(train_gen_vgg, validation_data=val_gen_vgg, epochs=EPOCHS, callbacks=[EarlyStopping(monitor='val_loss', patience=5, restore_best_weights=True)], verbose=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 4. Evaluation\n",
        "plot_history(history_vgg, \"VGG16\")\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- VGG16 Transfer Learning Report ---\")\n",
        "test_gen_vgg.reset() # Reset no gerador espec√≠fico do VGG\n",
        "y_pred_vgg = (model_vgg.predict(test_gen_vgg) > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()\n",
        "print(classification_report(test_gen_vgg.classes, y_pred_vgg, target_names=list(test_gen_vgg.class_indices.keys())))"
      ],

        "## üìä Final Comparative Analysis (Automated)\n",
        "This section evaluates all trained models on the Test Set to generate a consolidated performance table and comparison charts."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "vYZ2llqy9zTc"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# List of models and their respective generators\n",
        "# Ensure 'model_base', 'model_aug', 'model_deep', 'model_vgg' are defined in previous cells\n",
        "models_list = [\n",
        "    (\"1. Baseline\", model_base, test_gen),\n",
        "    (\"2. Data Augmentation\", model_aug, test_gen),\n",
        "    (\"3. Deep + Dropout\", model_deep, test_gen),\n",
        "    (\"4. Transfer Learning (VGG16)\", model_vgg, test_gen_vgg)\n",
        "]\n",
        "\n",
        "results_data = []\n",
        "confusion_matrices = []\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Generating final metrics and confusion matrices...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "for name, model, generator in models_list:\n",
        "    print(f\"Evaluating {name}...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 1. Basic Evaluation (Loss & Accuracy)\n",
        "    test_loss, test_acc = model.evaluate(generator, verbose=0)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 2. Generate Predictions\n",
        "    # Reset generator to ensure order matches y_true\n",
        "    generator.reset()\n",
        "    y_pred_probs = model.predict(generator, verbose=0)\n",
        "    y_pred = (y_pred_probs > 0.5).astype(int).flatten()\n",
        "    y_true = generator.classes\n",
        "\n",
        "    # 3. Specific Metrics\n",
        "    # We focus on Class 1 (VMD) Recall\n",
        "    vmd_recall = recall_score(y_true, y_pred, pos_label=1)\n",
        "    cm = confusion_matrix(y_true, y_pred)\n",
        "\n",
        "    results_data.append({\n",
        "        \"Model\": name,\n",
        "        \"Test Accuracy\": test_acc,\n",
        "        \"Test Loss\": test_loss,\n",
        "        \"VMD Recall\": vmd_recall\n",
        "    })\n",
        "    confusion_matrices.append((name, cm))\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Results Table ---\n",
        "df_results = pd.DataFrame(results_data)\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Final Results Table ---\")\n",
        "# Display with color gradient for better readability\n",
        "display(df_results.style.format({\n",
        "    \"Test Accuracy\": \"{:.2%}\",\n",
        "    \"Test Loss\": \"{:.4f}\",\n",
        "    \"VMD Recall\": \"{:.2%}\"\n",
        "}).background_gradient(cmap='Greens', subset=[\"Test Accuracy\", \"VMD Recall\"]))\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Visualization 1: Metrics Comparison ---\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(14, 5))\n",
        "\n",
        "# Accuracy Plot\n",
        "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
        "sns.barplot(data=df_results, x='Model', y='Test Accuracy', palette='viridis', hue='Model', legend=False)\n",
        "plt.title('Accuracy Comparison')\n",
        "plt.ylim(0, 1.1)\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
        "for index, row in df_results.iterrows():\n",
        "    plt.text(index, row['Test Accuracy'] + 0.02, f\"{row['Test Accuracy']:.2%}\", color='black', ha=\"center\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Recall Plot\n",
        "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
        "sns.barplot(data=df_results, x='Model', y='VMD Recall', palette='rocket', hue='Model', legend=False)\n",
        "plt.title('VMD Recall (Sensitivity) Comparison')\n",
        "plt.ylim(0, 1.1)\n",
        "plt.xticks(rotation=45)\n",
        "for index, row in df_results.iterrows():\n",
        "    plt.text(index, row['VMD Recall'] + 0.02, f\"{row['VMD Recall']:.2%}\", color='black', ha=\"center\")\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# --- Visualization 2: Confusion Matrices Grid (2x2) ---\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Confusion Matrices Comparison ---\")\n",
        "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))\n",
        "\n",
        "for i, (name, cm) in enumerate(confusion_matrices):\n",
        "    plt.subplot(2, 2, i + 1)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Extract False Negatives (Row 1, Col 0 in a standard binary CM)\n",
        "    # VMD is class 1. False Negative = True is VMD (1), Predicted is ND (0)\n",
        "    fn_count = cm[1, 0]\n",
        "\n",
        "    sns.heatmap(cm, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='Blues', cbar=False,\n",
        "                xticklabels=['ND', 'VMD'], yticklabels=['ND', 'VMD'])\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Highlight the Critical Error in the title\n",
        "    plt.title(f\"{name}\\n(VMD False Negatives: {fn_count})\", fontsize=11, fontweight='bold')\n",
        "    plt.xlabel('Predicted')\n",
        "    plt.ylabel('True')\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.tight_layout()\n",
        "plt.show()"
